social_posts.post_text: Turns out we will be doing some live musical performances this year! Unbelievably honored to be playing @inbetweendaysfestival in Quincy! So many Stellar musical groups all in one place. So, for all you East coasters come out and hang with us! Love you all so much!
Epic night with the Moody dudes playing songs for the Valentine's gathering, Earley doing a little Seeger and the night moves!

I recently did a super cool podcast with Brent @inlovingrecollection discussing the infamously bizarre album from 2007 Wild Mountain Nation. It was the album that allowed us to begin touring all over the place and to be honest, it was a very strange entryway into the music biz but I'm thankful there were people around who appreciated the crazy sideways reality of that record at the time. Check out the episode on all the platforms, peace and love to all.

East Coast fans heads up we are doing a gaggle of shows in August out your way! We will keep you updated as the dates get confirmed. @inbetweendaysfestival was kind enough to invite us to play, can't wait to do this, also been messing about in boats and started a new band called Inspirational Ambient Squirrel Riding a Unicorn. Peace!
Excited for this fantastic happening this summer! @moscowmountainmusicfest is having us out to play the sweet tunes and enjoy lots of other incredible artists! Hope to see any and all of you there!

Just wanted to let everyone know fyi, very excited for a handful of random shows happening in a couple weeks. Can't wait to get back on the road it's been quite a while and the music calls. We'll be playing some new tracks old tracks, some heart felt jams and any requests the attendees may have. Hope to see any and all of you out there, much love to all. Peace.

Oh and also, there are more dates throughout the world happening this year not a lot but a few choice ones. Stay tuned much love!

Heading out for parts unknown in a couple days, going to some funky spots to play some funky music and we've got some Low Ticket Warnings for @ashlandfolkcollective in Medford with @sharayasummers and Hood River @eventsattheruins with @cedarteethband !!!
Come feel the love, we desire your presence peace and love to all!!

Thanks Hood River and Boise for sell outs @theolympicboise and @eventsattheruins tonight! so psyched to hang here and jam some tunes with everybody, been a fabulous week on the road hanging @churchill.baker with artists of all stripes (got to check out the haunted basement of bizarre toys in Baker City) and all the cool bands @schellraiserfest stay aware and wonderful all you fans and peace!!

Also, new news coming possibly in lieu of new recorded sounds but don't quote me on that...
Teeny tiny bit of a new/old song about ex-cons and the dharma, the flow of light and energy and car theft. See you in Olympia this weekend. Peace.

Greetings denizens of the billion fold universe, I hope you are all doing well at peace and finding your way through this maze of joy, sorrow and silliness! This morning we are announcing the release of the new three song single Cheap Fantastical Takedown STREAMING NOW! Coming out on Oct 6....12-in Red vinyl only at Independent record stores! There's only 500 copies going on so get out there and get your copy! Overjoyed to be sharing this with you all thanks to the lovely @yeproc for putting this out into the world. We also have some shows happening in the midwest this fall, so excited! Stay tuned...

Much love to all who partook of the new single! Final shows of 2023 happening out in the Midwest, reliably transcendent jams will occur and we'd love all our Midwest people to be there!! There will be new merch shirts and stickers and swag for all, be excellent to each other and Peace!!

15 years ago this month we released Furr, thanks to @subpop records and it changed our lives, got us on the road for many years. I just unearthed the original lyrics to the title track written in an old black notebook back in 2007. Funny to see all the changes I made in the lyrics, some of my thought process leaking through on those old yellow pages. It's the kind of song that took on a life of its own. It was an honor to make that song and record it and release it for all of you. If anyone has a good story about the first time they heard Furr I'd love to hear it! Much love..

We’re only a few short weeks out from Mempho Presents: BAM! Wiseacre Beer and Music Festival featuring @blitzentrapper !! Ticket link in bio

Blitzen Trapper's latest album, "Holy Smokes Future Jokes," explores profound cosmic themes, delving into the intermediate state between human lives and the escape from the cycle of birth and rebirth. Led by front man Eric Earley, the Portland-based band has spent two decades crafting a unique musical catalog that ranges from impressionistic melodies to electrified rhythms, celebrating the full spectrum of the human experience.

Rooted in folk-rock sensibilities, the music combines fingerpicked guitars and acoustic instrumentation. Despite its heavy subject matter, "Holy Smokes Future Jokes" is more concerned with illumination than darkness, offering a captivating and magical journey through the profound and the unsettling, all captured within the band's introspective and personal perspective.
Heading down to Memphis tomorrow folks see you there!

So I quit music and have become an accountant and now I can finally sleep at night, just kidding LOL just spent the weekend shooting an extremely bizarre wacky music video with @mychals and @iamleomoon_ which includes fake blood and puppets. Look for BT weirdness coming throughout this new year. Happy New Year's to everyone, love you all!!
